<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-613] Wrong number of JUnit4 tests when running in parallel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-613</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a test class with three test methods, out of which two fail. When running sequentially, I get the following output, which is correct in my opinion:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;===&lt;br/&gt;
Tests run: 3, Failures: 2, Errors 0, Skipped 0, ....&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Results:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Failed tests:&lt;br/&gt;
   a(...)&lt;br/&gt;
   b(...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests run: 3, Failures: 2, Errors: 0, Skipped: 0&lt;br/&gt;
===&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then I switch to parallel execution:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;=== pom.xml ===&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;plugin&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;maven-surefire-plugin&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;version&amp;gt;2.5.&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;parallel&amp;gt;classes&amp;lt;/parallel&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/plugin&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
===============&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This gives me the following output from the same test class:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;===&lt;br/&gt;
Tests run: 2, Failures: 2, Errors, 0, Skipped: 0 ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Results :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Failed tests:&lt;br/&gt;
   a(...)&lt;br/&gt;
   b(...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests run: 2, Failures: 2, Errors: 0, Skipped: 0&lt;br/&gt;
===&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same problem occurs with &quot;&amp;lt;parallel&amp;gt;methods&amp;lt;/parallel&amp;gt;&quot; and &quot;&amp;lt;parallel&amp;gt;tests&amp;lt;/parallel&amp;gt;&quot;. When running a bunch of tests, the reported number of tests is lower than the actual number of tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Am I missing something, or is this a bug?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Cygwin&lt;br/&gt;
Maven 2.0.9&lt;br/&gt;
Maven Surefire plugin 2.5&lt;br/&gt;
JUnit 4.8.1</environment>
