                            <comment id="14454588" author="krosenvold" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 08:23:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The parallel junit provider requires legal junit-tests (as opposed to the classic junit4-provider). Make sure all your test methods are annotated with @Test or they will not be run.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14454482" author="mag" created="Fri, 23 Apr 2010 02:56:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Demo project illustrating the wrong number of executed tests for parallel execution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14454517" author="mag" created="Fri, 23 Apr 2010 03:05:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Kristian, thank you for your quick response.&lt;br/&gt;
The problem seems to be with the surefire plugin 2.5 and only arises when the tests run in parallel. The number of tests is fine when parallel execution is switched off. The tests are correctly annotated. I attached a small demo project that shows the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14454508" author="krosenvold" created="Mon, 3 May 2010 15:30:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in r940602: Junit 4.7 provider does not count tests correctly in all circumstances.    &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Updated DemultiplexingRunListener to non-ketchup-bottle variety that logs output smoothly per completed test.&lt;br/&gt;
Added IT&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
